uration. I wonder if just using `Class.forName` is sufficient, or if we need to include subsequent members. The report mentions `trackedApi`, so I’ll need to check the native generated reflect config to see if it has relevant stack information.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yE1QRMLdQo6bSpxdzacuVeBN|fc_0c962416b488006e016a28816a84188193bcd15825a1378708", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/native -type f \\( -name 'reflect-config.json' -o -name '*trace*' -o -name '*config*json' \\) | head -80", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 815, "output": 1083, "cacheRead": 82944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 84842, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781039431456, "responseId": "resp_0c962416b488006e016a28814803f881938adbbab07d8b1c9e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_yE1QRMLdQo6bSpxdzacuVeBN|fc_0c962416b488006e016a28816a84188193bcd15825a1378708", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/native/generated/generateTestResourcesConfigFile/resource-config.json\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781039467204}]}
